Author: BENDER_ICO
Title: [PRE-ANN] BRIXBY -blockchain marketplace for transportation services.
Body: Hello, my name is Vladislav, I am member of the Jury.Online team. We are going to make an offer for your ICO. We are in touch with Venture Funds which are interested in investing into some projects via our system. It will work in that way: investors will put funds on a smart contract, which will be available as you will go through arranged milestones. Thus, as you finished point of the road map you will get additional investments from the smart contract. As a result, it will decrease risk of the project and make it much attractive. In addition, there will be arbitrage possibility  to solve a dispute situation. I'd be glad to tell you more about this protocol. My contacts: Telegram @BDLR14  Email vladislaw.usov@gmail.com

Title: [PRE-ANN] BRIXBY -blockchain marketplace for transportation services.
Body: Hi Vladislav, sounds interesting.  I will write you on email above.

Author: Crypto_Enthusiast
Title: [PRE-ANN] BRIXBY -blockchain marketplace for transportation services.
Body: Hi Dev, There are a lot of transport service providers. This means that competitors will either align prices, or dumping. Will there be uniform rules for suppliers to protect consumers from doubtful competition?

Author: Alex Sol
Title: [PRE-ANN] BRIXBY -blockchain marketplace for transportation services.
Body: Hi, thanks for these questions, this is really important to comprehend.  Wrote you a deliberate answer , hope it will become clear.  Currently some functionality of the product is already successfully implemented in our platform, which is commercially used in Russia, Cyprus, Belarus, and Kazakhstan. The goal of ICO for Brixby is expedited development of additional universal features and rewriting platform on blockchain -this will allow us reach our goal of launching platform globally. We are planning to do the blockchain based platform pilot prior to the commercial launch in three countries: India, Kazakhstan, and Mombasa - this all before 2019. By 2019 we shall have a well-functioning and pilot tested planning, this will allow for a rapid global launch of decentralised platform as described in Brixby whitepaper. The acquired tokens will give the platform users the right to use the platform as soon as the basic features are released, we believe we are able to do it in the next 6 months and make secured transactions.

Author: Alex Sol
Title: [PRE-ANN] BRIXBY -blockchain marketplace for transportation services.
Body: Hi Crypto_Enthusiast, this was one of the major things for our business modeling, for the moment we stand on the point that we provide a market place, it is up to service providers to set prices. All the service providers will be rated, thus the quality of s service provider will be seen. In the future, if Brixby has enough market power, we may consider setting up thr prices in our markets, as Uber does for instance.

Author: Alex Sol
Title: [PRE-ANN] BRIXBY -blockchain marketplace for transportation services.
Body: Hello! We are preparing blockchain based marketplace for transportation services, which has a goal to couple private transportation providers and end users.  The project is called Brixby  WEBSITE  We are building a platform where people could rent a vehicle, park it, charge electric car (EV) and pay for those transportation services at one place. Small businesses will list their assets (a vehicle, a parking space, a bus service, a charger, etc.) on BRIXBY and start earning money from their peers. why blockchain: confirmed financial transactions, transparency, no need for extra reconciliation.  WHITEPAPER OF THE PROJECT   Project is backed by real working successful IT business solving transportation problems. Learn more in TEAM section.  There are 2 main groups of Brixby users: businesses and consumers. Microbusiness and SME in transportation sector are among the main BRIXBY users. What makes BRIXBY truly beautiful is the ability to combine any number of services into a product or solution one needs. Business may choose as many core services as they need or use user interfaces or business services instead.  Features  One easy to use app Parking, EV charging, car sharing, tickets sales, etc. — one Brixby app can do it all with great UX. Managing transportation services and payments Management system, instant payments for microbusiness. Blockchain made it possible to avoid payment mistakes. Full transparency Blockchain based, full control of all your transactions Connecting microbusinesses Approach to private sector through franchisees. Quick plag-in of microbusiness’s assets. Global platform for local transportation needs Existing solutions are often ultralocal. Brixby allows to use local infrastructure in any place of the world with one app. Localization and customization Seller (microbusiness) or third party can use Brixby API to create his own applications for their businesses   There will be pre-ICO pre-sale and ICO.  Currently can you please give your comments and criticisms on white paper?  We also welcome different new participants of the team. Please write me PM about your desirable participation, about your skills and desirable compensation.   =========================================================  TOKEN - BRICK  TOKEN DETAILS Total Supply: 158 523 442 Type: ERC-20 Pre-Sale Token Supply: 4 000 000 (~2,5%) Pre-Sale Cap: 500 ETH (~$150k) Pre-Sale BONUS: up to 50% Bonus  ICO Token Supply: 154 523 442 (~97,5%) BRICKS DURING ICO   Token Distribution Breakdown:  2.5% of all tokens will be available for purchase during our Pre-Sale, and there will be up to 50% bonus. 70% of all tokens will be available for purchase during the pre-ICO and ICO. The rest of the total supply of tokens equals to 30% - for partners, lawyers, the team and pre-ICO. Tokens of founders are not transferable upon ICO completion: locked up for 6 months by a smart contract function.  =========================================================  BOUNTIES for TRANSLATIONS, COMMUNITY MANAGEMENT, BITCOINTALK ACTIVITIES  – we are in process Community management includes communication with mass media.  =========================================================  SOCIAL NETWORKS  Facebook  TeleGram  =========================================================  TECHNOLOGY  There are five main layers of BRIXBY architecture: •   Core microservices •   Business services •   User/Applications interfaces •   3rd party interfaces •   Smart contracts  =========================================================  TEAM  Daniil Titarenko - Co-Founder & CEO Denis Ambatenne - Co-Founder & CTO Andrey Boldin - Co-Founder & CFO Olga Gavrilenko - Law & Regulation Anton Rumyantsev - Front-End Team Lead Mikhail Pokidko - Back-End Team Lead Alexander Solovyev – Marketing consultant  More info about people  ADVISORS  Vitaly Gumirov - The founder of Miniapps.pro Linkedin  Oleg Raspopov - Vice-President of MTS (Foreign subsidiaries) Linkedin   LAUNCHED PROJECTS  Parking projects A digital parking payment operator in the USA serving 40+ municipalities, universities, and private operators, whose mission is to develop and introduce new, innovative software applications for the parking and transport industry, as well as any other sector where the handling of permits and tickets is required. www.mobile-now.com  A digital marketplace that aggregates various parking services in all segments of the market (public car parks, private car parks and on-street parking), to offer them via a smartphone application and a website. Currently works in France, Spain, Belgium and Brazil. www.opngo.com  A digital parking payment operator in Macedonia. www.parking.mk  Moscow’s primary centrally-digitized parking solution with the largest paid parking area in the world. www.parking.mos.ru  Parking operator in Kazakhstan. www.aparking.kz  Parking operator in Belarus. www.parkme.by  Digital parking payment operator in Ukraine. www.516.com.ua   EV-charging projects In the Netherlands, a superfast EV charging operator that builds charging stations for electric vehicles directly along the highway with the goal of having charging network expand throughout Europe. www.fastned.nl  An electromobility programme in Estonia that promotes emission-free personal transportation and electric cars in order to achieve energy efficiency, fuel independence, and a better environment. www.elmo.ee  EV charging operator in Russia. www.chargeyourcar.ru  Car sharing The first and biggest project in Finland to offer affordable, easy-to-use, zero-emission car rentals and ridesharing services. All vehicles are 100% electric and completely CO2 emission-free. Shared and rented EVs contribute to better, cleaner city air, and also save money for their users. www.ekorent.fi    *** Please keep in mind : this is a pre-announce topic ***  I will do my best to answer your questions in this topic

Author: Alex Sol
Title: [PRE-ANN] BRIXBY -blockchain marketplace for transportation services.
Body: And speaking about EV-charging in Europe , and Germany particullary we have this encouraging stats from platts.com  The number of charging points for electric vehicles in Germany has reached 10,700 almost doubling on the year, underlining the up-front efforts by utilities for the mass roll-out of electric vehicles, German utility group BDEW said Monday.  77,000 charging points needed for 1 million EVs Survey boosted by including parking house operators Utility lobby says 'car industry needs to deliver now'  According to the semi-annual survey, which now also includes operators of parking spaces, over 3,300 new charging points were added so far this year.  Of the total only 530 are so-called fast-charging points (above 22 kW), it said.  "These figures impressively demonstrate that the energy industry is pushing ahead at a rapid pace on this front with a massive up-front effort," BDEW chief Stefan Kapferer said, adding that given the slow adoption rate of electric vehicles it is now up to the automotive industry to bring attractive models onto the market.  So the lack is more than 60k charging spots!
